value.value: A position, opinion or judgment reached after consideration by a research subject.
An administrative or territorial division of a county, state, country or city based on a shared characteristic.
Any of various devices and systems designed to track a patient's condition.
The name of the person acting as a channel for communication between groups or on behalf of a group.

A computing system (inspired by biological neural networks) that learns (progressively improves its ability) to do tasks by considering examples without task-specific programming. (After DeepAI Machine Learning Glossary and Terms)
The determination of the amount of cholic acid, glycocholic acid, hyocholic acid, and taurocholic acid in a sample.
The multiple layers of specialized tissue that surround the cavity of the gastrointestinal tract, including the mucosa, submucosa, muscular layers, and serosa.
Any lymph node within the lower gastrointestinal tract.
The ratio of two concentration values.

value.value: The ratio of two AUC from T1 to T2 values.

label.value: Ratio AUC to Last Nonzero Concentration

value.value: The ratio of two AUC to last nonzero concentration values.
The determination of the amount of ursodeoxycholic acid, glycoursodeoxycholic acid, tauroursodeoxycholic acid, and epimerized ursodeoxycholic acid in a sample.
The determination of the amount of chenodeoxycholic acid, glycochenodeoxycholic acid, and taurochenodeoxycholic acid in a sample.
Picture Archiving and Communication System: A network established to provide access, storage and retrieval of images from medical imaging instrumentation.
The determination of the amount of lithocholic acid, glycolithocholic acid, and taurolithocholic acid in a sample.
The portion of the gastrointestinal tract wall that surrounds the cavities of the duodenum, jejunum, ileum, colon, rectum, and anus.
A response about the amount of time that something exists or that something requires.
A response about an individual's difficulties.
A response about an individual's agreement about something.
A response that something never happens or is never true.
A response about an individual's pain.
A response about an individual's extremity pain.
A response about an individual's cough.
A response about an individual's hearing.
A response about an individual's level of satisfaction.
An angiosarcoma that arises from the breast parenchyma and is not associated with radiation exposure.
A response about an individual's sexual activity.

A self-limiting, rapidly growing, non-encapsulated benign neoplasm that arises from the breast. It has been described in both the subcutis and parenchyma of the breast. It occurs most frequently in the upper-outer quadrant. It is composed of fibroblastic/myofibroblastic cells.
A response about an individual's walking ability.
An angiolipoma that arises from the breast. The majority are located in the subcutaneous tissue overlying the breast parenchyma, rather than in breast parenchyma.
A response about time spent on an activity.

A trial in which data capture, administration of medication, and possibly other procedures are done at the subject's location, e.g., at home or by telemedicine, mobile technology, and local HCPs (like family physicians, general practitioners). (After CTTI Recommendations: Decentralized Clinical Trials, September 2018)

A subset of machine learning that is part of the broader family of machine learning methodologies based on artificial neural networks. A deep neural network has multiple layers between input and output layers to progressively extract higher level features from the raw input. (After DeepAI Machine Learning Glossary and Terms)

The degree to which an individual has the capacity to obtain, communicate, process, and understand basic health information and services to make health decisions. (After The Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act of 2010, Title V; After What is Health Literacy? Oct 23, 2019)
A flexible fiber-optic probe that is used to examine the last 12-25 inches of the large intestine.

The use of algorithms to determine properties of natural, human language so that computers can understand what humans have written or said. NLP includes teaching computer systems how to extract data from bodies of written text, translate from one language to another, and recognize printed or handwritten words. (After DeepAI Definitions)
A stage in the sequence of activities in a clinical study.
Writing that is clear, concise, well-organized, and follows other best practices appropriate to the subject or field and intended audience. (Plain Writing Act of 2010)
Data that are artificially created rather than being generated by actual events.
A state in which two or more individuals are connected but not physically co-located.
A dataset containing data that is used for adverse event analyses.
The act or process by which the study product is obtained by the study site or investigator.
The act or process for documenting the storage, inventory tracking, and disposition of the study product.
The composition of the study product, which may include active and inactive ingredients, dose, and dosage form.
The outward or visible aspect of the study product.
A tuft of material on the end of a stick for applying solutions and suspensions
The material type and configuration used to contain the study product.
The written, printed, or graphic matter on, or accompanying, the study product or its packaging.
The physical or environmental conditions under which the study product is maintained.
